INTERSHOP IOM 4.0.0-SNAPSHOT Database Model   (revision 56e211c17f383a5356bafbd3b32a94e8539d520f)

Table oms.Supplier2ReturnTypeDefDO

Return types that should be used by a supplier.
Additionally information for RMA code generation can be configured for each return type.

Columns 

References[1] Column Type Constraints[2] Default Comment
id bigint PK, UNIQUE, NOT_NULL  
ReturnTypeDefDO returnTypeDefRef integer The return type that should be used by the supplier. 
supplierReturnTypeName varchar(50) The name of the return type as used by the supplier instead of defaults. Example "Return" 
SupplierDO supplierRef bigint The supplier the return type should be used for. 
rmaNo varchar(50) Static return number that should be sent for the supplier and this return type. 
preselected boolean NOT_NULL false Whether the return type should be preselected when creating a return in the OMT. 
rmaCodeCounter varchar(30) Latest generated RMA number. Only relevant if IOM generates RMA numbers for the supplier. 
rmaCodeStart varchar(30) Start value of RMA number. Only relevant if IOM generates RMA numbers for the supplier. 
rmaCodeEnd varchar(30) Maximum value of RMA number. Only relevant if IOM generates RMA numbers for the supplier. 
interval integer RMA number generating interval. Only relevant if IOM generates RMA numbers for the supplier. 
modificationDate timestamp without time zone  
startDate timestamp without time zone Start date of current RMA number generation. Only relevant if IOM generates RMA numbers for the supplier. 
minEndDate timestamp without time zone Date on which the RMA numbers do not repeat. Only relevant if IOM generates RMA numbers for the supplier. 
ejbLookup varchar(500) Lookup path to the implementation of the RMA number generation. Possibility to register a customized RMA number session bean.
